content: Love the game outside of 2 issues. 1- 90% of trade negotiations end on the first round of negotiations if the first offer isn't accepted (as both buyer and seller) 2- When selling an academy player their value is always $0 so there's no value in raising academy players to sell. replyContent: Thanks for your feedback. Regarding the value of academy players - as soon as they start to play more games and gain more experience, their value will increase rapidly. It will obviously take a few seasons for your young players to reach their potential and their full value, but be patient and you'll be able to make your youth system a success!

replyContent:
Hi Simon, the game has a built-in protection to try to stop people clicking buttons too fast (eg before their device has processed the previous action). If you do this, the buttons become disabled for around 2 seconds.

So if the game seems to freeze or any of the buttons seem to stop working, just leave it for a few seconds before trying again.

replyContent: Hi Michael, you can place players on the loan list at any point during the game. Just go to the squad page, then choose the player, and the click the "Transfer" button at the bottom right. That will bring up a few options, including "Available for loan".

Although, I've lost a few hours just playing the game, it's very fun and addictive. Given the number of football manager and chairman games nowadays that seem to be so in depth and somewhat complicated by excessive attributes (skill, positioning, concentration et cetera), more straightforward games like this would be appreciated. So, spend the few quid and enjoy the simplicity.

This is a great game but I can think of a few small improvements to enhance the players experience:   1. Have a way to encourage the manager to play specific players who aren't getting game time so that you don't lose them on contract expiry.  2. Be able to set out your expectations of a manager at the beginning of a season or when a new one comes in. This could be as simple as choosing from a list "aim for playoffs" "win a domestic cup" ect.  3. Be able to change the ticket prices mid season. This adds more flexibility as to how you manage your finances and could be utilised to avoid bankruptcy.  4. Ways to invest money over seasons (up to 10). So that you could generate more income to assist in building your squad.  These are all small improvements but would make the in game experience more realistic.

This game is a con. I too enjoyed the game at first. So much so, that I purchased the full game, bought the Super Stadium, spent money on club investments many times. Throughout all that you STILL LOSE ALL YOUR MONEY EVERY SEASON. 120,000 crowds at full ticket prices and you STILL LOSE ALL YOUR MONEY EVERY SEASON. This is a con designed to get you to fork out your money to purchase more club investments.  You will get your manager, players, facilities all up to 99 and, most of the time, you will be around 10+ points behind the league leaders.  My recommended wage limit is ¬£1.75m. In order to achieve that, my squad would have to be around 90% youth players as most 99 rated players will be around ¬£150k+ a week in wages. This, I remind you, is with 120,000 crowds, at full ticket prices. So to summarise.  You will achieve everything.  99 rated squad and manager.  99 rated facilities.  120,000 Super Stadium.  And you will STILL LOSE ALL YOUR MONEY EVERY SEASON.  Unless, of course, you keep forking out your OWN MONEY to purchase club investment.  And therein lies the con.
replyContent: Hi Paul, if your club is losing money like that every season you're doing something badly wrong as chairman. Many of our users have built clubs who make millions of pounds in profit ever year, without ever spending "real" money in the game. Contact us via http://www.football-chairman.com/#contact and we'll help you work out what you're doing wrong.

An interesting slant on the crowded football management genre. Instead of playing as the club's manager, you play as the chairman.  This frees you from often laborious tasks of moving injured players in and out of the squad, or playing trial and error with different combinations of tactics. This is all taken care of for you by your manager.  As a result, you are left to take care of the fun stuff like building up your stadium, choosing which players to buy and sell, and managing your finances. Really enjoying this game.

I reckon that there should be more interactive features e.g. between Chairman and his manager- like when the team has gone into a bad patch and the manager gives him an ultimatum and different backroom staff offer better strengths or point increases to the manager. They should perhaps be tine to time Chairman to manager chats like telling the manager what he expects from the manager e.g. emphasis on younger players or experience or rotation etc. I have had my manager come to me asking to buy a whole lot of players who are mediocre and old despite me giving him a lot of money to buy the 'world', or leaving good players on the bench the entire season and then they want to leave.  One area I find funny, is that my manager would buy a player and then let him go a couple of weeks later...I have had that happen a few times. Sometimes I feel there may be a glitch as most times when an opponent has a player sent off they seem to win the match after that.

I played the lite version of this game a while and came back to it after a spell (babies apparently take up a lot of free time). I went ahead and purchased the full version and have not regretted it one bit. The game is perfect for my commute to work, and being able to create my own league is deeply appreciated. The only knocks I have on the game are: (1) all too often an offer is made to purchase a player of mine who I feel the need to keep. I reject the offer, only to find that my manager wants to acquire a better player at that position on a free transfer! Or I sell a player while negotiating a salary with a better player, only for him to refuse the contract and then I'm short one player. It would help to know if I will bring the new player on before selling the other player. (2) the controls along the bottom of the screen are right where I place my thumbs at rest. Sometimes this will lead to inadvertent player moves. But all of that bring said, the game is rock solid and is exactly what I want in a sports app!

All of the in-app purchases are 100% optional - at no point does the game force anyone to spend real money. If your club goes bust, start again and try some different tactics!
